pullRequest.body:
Add lemmas to rewrite the sum/difference of two `indicatorConstLp` with same support. The distance between to Lp functions is the same as the norm of their difference (even if $p < 1$ and it's not a norm).

bors r+

Thanks!

bors r+
I don't think this lemma is worthwhile adding since its just an direct application of `apply_indicator_symmDiff`.

Well indeed it is a direct application, but I thought it would be useful to have it directly. I prove equality of functions, so if I am doing some rewrites with functions which are not evaluated I don't have to stop the `rw`. In my proof of `norm_indicatorConstLp_sub`, if I do not use `norm_indicator_symmDiff`, I have to do something like this:
```lean
import Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.LpSpace

open ENNReal symmDiff MeasureTheory

theorem norm_indicatorConstLp_sub {α E : Type*} [MeasurableSpace α] {μ : Measure α}
    {s t : Set α} (hs : MeasurableSet s) (ht : MeasurableSet t) (hμs : μ s ≠ ∞) (hμt : μ t ≠ ∞)
    [NormedAddCommGroup E] (c : E)
    (hp_ne_zero : p ≠ 0) (hp_ne_top : p ≠ ∞) :
    ‖indicatorConstLp p hs hμs c - indicatorConstLp p ht hμt c‖ =
    ‖c‖ * (μ (s ∆ t)).toReal ^ (1 / p.toReal) := by
  rw [indicatorConstLp, indicatorConstLp, ← Memℒp.toLp_sub, Lp.norm_toLp,
    ← snorm_norm]
  simp_rw [Pi.sub_apply, ← Set.apply_indicator_symmDiff norm_neg]
  rw [snorm_norm, snorm_indicator_const (hs.symmDiff ht) hp_ne_zero hp_ne_top, ENNReal.toReal_mul,
    toReal_coe_nnnorm, ← ENNReal.toReal_rpow]
```
So I stop the `rw` to make a `simp_rw` instead.
Also `norm_indicator_symmDiff` is very similar to `abs_indicator_symmDiff` just above, which is the same with absolute value, so I thought it would make sense to have it with the norm as well.
Tell me if you still think I should remove that lemma.

On second thought, I see what you mean. I do not have a lot of experience and I do not like to stop a `rw` a sequence because some lemma is not exactly in the right form, but I cannot add every lemma to have exactly the right form.

```suggestion
  simp_rw [indicatorConstLp, ← Memℒp.toLp_add, indicator_add]
```

Same below

```suggestion
theorem indicatorConstLp_add {c' : E} :
```

`hμs` is already in the variables, and `c'` should be implicit since `c` is. Same below.

Since you said you would prefer a single sequence of rewrite, here's how I would do it:
```suggestion
  simp_rw [indicatorConstLp, ← Memℒp.toLp_sub, Lp.norm_toLp, ← snorm_norm (F := E),
    Pi.sub_apply, ← apply_indicator_symmDiff norm_neg, snorm_norm, 
    snorm_indicator_const (hs.symmDiff ht) hp_ne_zero hp_ne_top, ENNReal.toReal_mul,
    toReal_coe_nnnorm, ← ENNReal.toReal_rpow]
```

Note the key trick to force `F := E` to prevent an infinite loop when rewriting by `← snorm_norm`.

```suggestion
theorem norm_indicatorConstLp_sub {t : Set α} {ht : MeasurableSet t} {hμt : μ t ≠ ∞}
```
Since the situation is symmetric between `s` and `t` the explicitness of the assumptions should match. The reason everything can be implicit here is that most of the time you will rewrite from left to right, hence the hypotheses needed already apply in the expression.

I wrote it this way because it was done that way in similar theorems below (e.g. [MeasureTheory.dist_indicatorConstLp_eq_norm](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSpace.html#MeasureTheory.dist_indicatorConstLp_eq_norm)), should I change those too? And in fact I realized this result gave me a much simpler proof, but makes me question the interest of the theorem.

Indeed I think these should be changed as well (and that should be easy since they're not used). Regarding the usefulness of the theorem, indeed I think the existing result is somewhat better as it's the best statement you can hope for without side conditions, and doing two rewrites instead of one is not a big deal in practice. Would you be okay with dropping this in favor of the existing result?
Yes I'll do that!

However I did not find a lemma to rewrite the norm as a distance, because `Lp E p mu` is not a normed group if `p < 1` so [dist_eq_norm](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Basic.html#dist_eq_norm) does not work, do you see a better way than doing a `change`?
I just added this as a theorem.

Yes I think that was the best thing to do, we already have some duplicates like [MeasureTheory.Lp.norm_neg](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/LpSpace.html#MeasureTheory.Lp.norm_neg).
